    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">When we assign these variables to other variables using <code>=</code>, we <strong>copy </strong>the value to the new variable. They are copied by value.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="iframe"><pre><span>var x = 10;<br/>var y = 'abc';</span><span>var a = x;<br/>var b = y;</span><span>console.log(x, y, a, b); // -&gt; 10, 'abc', 10, 'abc'</span></pre></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Both <code>a</code> and <code>x</code> now contain <code>10</code>. Both <code>b</code> and <code>y</code> now contain <code>'abc'</code>. They’re separate, as the values themselves were copied.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
